Description: Fragment of a fluted side of a moulding (?); two pieces re-joined.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, Very probably from the "Qasr", passage between the two casemate buildings A and B
Curator's comments: 1887,0101.1413, 1887,0101.1414 and 1887,0101.1415 are made of the same stone and belong probably to the same architectural decoration, probably parts of the "cornice and fluted moulding of limestone around the top of ...wall" of the open-air court at the entrance of the casemate building B of the "Qasr", mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 56 § 55.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 56 § 55)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.43, p.55, p.176, pl.18)
